      "widgets_values": [
        "DECIMATE TO A BUDGET — real-time / WebGL / file-size target.\n\nPipeline: Solve → DepthMap → DeriveReliefMesh → (viewport preview +\nAtlasExportReliefMesh with retopo_method DECIMATE, target 1500).\n\nDECIMATE = quadric decimation via fast-simplification (backing\ntrimesh.simplify_quadric_decimation). Pure decimation, no remeshing —\nkeeps the original topology class, just fewer faces. The node targets\n~2× this in faces (decimate is face-count-driven). Vertex count changes\n→ projection-baked UVs are REGENERATED from the recovered camera so the\nlight mesh stays textured (pure numpy).\n\nNeeds the fast-simplification package (BSD, CPU-only, macOS arm64 wheels):\n    pip install fast-simplification\nMissing it → actionable ImportError (swap to 'smooth' to run without it).\n\nThe AtlasBlockoutViewport shows the DENSE derived mesh (use_solve_mesh keeps\nthe viewport on the un-decimated projection mesh); the export is the light,\nretopologized-for-budget OBJ. retopo_target_vertex_count is the lever —\ndrop it for a real-time asset, raise it for a hero DCC handoff."
      ],
      "title": "Note"
    }
